  <description type="morphology">Woody stems erect or procumbent, creeping and sometimes rooting at base, 10–50 cm;
        stems sparingly to much-branched, younger branches with fleshy segments 5–20 × 2–4 mm.
        Terminal spikes: larger with 12–40 segments, 20–85 mm. Fertile segments: larger 2–4.5 ×
        2.5–3.8 mm; central flowers 1.6–2.8 × 1–2.5 mm; anthers 0.7–1 mm. Seeds 1.2–1.5 mm,
        pubescent; hairs curved or hooked, longer hairs 1–2 mm.</description>
